fix: bad definition of glyphs between 0x400 and 0x7ff

Issue #117

fix: set the font abc2svg.ttf as installable

Reported by Nicolas Boulenguez
configure: forbid globs and undefined expansions
configure: report unknown arguments

Allow cross builds via a --host=GNU_TYPE configure option

The given prefix is added to CC and PKG_CONFIG.
Tell ./configure to fail on first unexpected non-zero exit status

Improve readability in ./configure with single assignments

For readability of the data flow, replace some successive assignments
(CPPFLAGS, LDLIBS) with intermediate variables.

Reduce duplication in configure script

For as many variables as possible, write the default value near the
name so that the list is not duplicated.

Expand some variables recursively in Makefile instead of sequentially
in ./configure.
Move some C syntax from configure to config.h.in
